I love coming to Broadway Food Hall for poke bowls at King Kuma! They are very generous with their servings and the service is always very kind and quick. I would recommend the tuna poke bowl, though the salmon and tofu bowls are also excellent. Their sushi rolls are also very delicious when they are offered!  I have also attended a few of the events here, including their wine tastings and private social gatherings. The venue is great for a crowd and there are different offerings to please all palates! If you have the opportunity to attend an event - public or private - don't hesitate.  Lunch rush is real here. While parking is a little hard on the lot, there is plenty of street parking available. Because of the several offerings inside, the lines typically move quickly, and you usually would never have a longer wait than 5-10 minutes (at most!). Enjoy!

We contracted with the charming Broadway Food Hall for my daughter's July, 2019, wedding reception and we are entirely pleased with every aspect of our dealings with Matt and his professional and friendly staff from start to finish. After researching many venues throughout the Champaign-Urbana area, I don't believe you'll find a more reasonable option for a wedding reception. Their food and drink prices are beyond fair considering the amount of guests and the quality and taste are truly outstanding!  They were very easy to work with throughout the planning process and on the day of the event, everything was exactly as we had organized together. Most impressive was that everything was served in a timely manner - the dinner hour took one hour with all of the guests receiving their family-style platters at the same time.  The entire event received praise from guests and I wholeheartedly recommend BFH to anyone looking for just somewhere to eat OR to host an event that goes beyond the typically-generic event spaces and provides something uniquely urban-chic and yet comfortable to all attendees.
